No, this is the wrong bus.

48:05.720 --> 48:09.391
This is for players.
You ride with the cheerleaders.

48:17.565 --> 48:21.319
- Stef? Stef? Okay.
- Hey, Lisa, don't talk to me now.

48:21.486 --> 48:24.239
- I want to be left alone.
- You were good.

48:24.406 --> 48:26.866
Just leave me alone!

48:46.428 --> 48:52.350
Why didn't Nickerson take
the safety and then punt it out of there?

48:52.517 --> 48:57.397
Because he's an asshole. We're never
gonna beat those rich pricks.

48:57.564 --> 49:02.861
Not as long as he's coach we won't.
- Maybe that won't be for too long.

49:05.738 --> 49:08.324
Goddamn it, it's true.

49:08.491 --> 49:12.704
He's kicked off for disciplinary
reasons. What does that mean?

49:12.871 --> 49:16.207
- His big mouth got him in trouble.
- What'd he say?

49:16.374 --> 49:18.877
He knew this would ruin his chances.

49:19.043 --> 49:24.507
Word gets around he has a bad attitude,
he'll be lucky if he gets any offers.

49:24.674 --> 49:27.427
I can't believe he meant it.
Everybody's-

49:27.594 --> 49:29.929
Your kid cost us the game.

49:33.683 --> 49:35.602
Oh! Hot damn!

49:35.768 --> 49:38.980
I'm gonna go home and wait
for your brother.

49:39.147 --> 49:42.567
Because whatever he said,
he'll have to apologize.

49:42.734 --> 49:45.403
Sure, Pop. Sure.

49:47.071 --> 49:49.157
Goddamn!

50:08.134 --> 50:09.719
Hey! Hey!

50:10.011 --> 50:14.015
Hey, Stefie, come on in.
All right.

51:15.159 --> 51:18.037
Suzie?
Uh-huh?

51:18.204 --> 51:20.581
I should've had Rifleman
fall on the ball.

51:22.458 --> 51:26.879
Please, Vern,
you're driving yourself crazy.

51:27.046 --> 51:32.093
Daddy, there's a man playing
on the lawn, and he waked me up.

51:32.260 --> 51:35.346
Honey, you get in bed with Mommy,
okay?

51:44.021 --> 51:45.690
Hey.

51:46.858 --> 51:49.777
Bosko.
What the hell are you guys doing?

51:49.986 --> 51:53.281
What do you think?
- Isn't this a little crazy?

51:53.448 --> 51:56.033
You gonna do something about it?

52:22.560 --> 52:24.312
Bastards.

52:38.075 --> 52:39.535
Hey, Stef!

52:39.952 --> 52:42.079
- Hey.
- How you doing?

52:42.246 --> 52:46.125
- You going to talk to the coach?
- Yeah. Wish me luck.

52:46.292 --> 52:49.253
- Want me to go with you?
- No.

52:49.462 --> 52:50.963
You sure?

52:51.130 --> 52:54.800
- Okay, good luck, pal.
- All right.

52:56.219 --> 52:57.678
Hey.

52:58.804 --> 53:01.599
- How you doing, man?
- How you doing?

53:15.613 --> 53:17.406
Coach Nickerson.

53:21.953 --> 53:27.458
I'd just like to say I'm sorry about
what I said. I didn't mean anything.

53:28.709 --> 53:33.673
And, well, Friday, it's our last game,
it's at home, and I'm a senior.

53:33.839 --> 53:37.718
I'd really like to play,
and it means a lot to me.

53:37.885 --> 53:43.224
And I feel really bad
about what happened.

53:43.391 --> 53:47.103
I was hoping maybe you'd take me
back on the team.

53:47.645 --> 53:48.938
I'm sorry.

53:51.983 --> 53:53.651
So what?

53:56.904 --> 53:59.281
Real forgiving, aren't you?

54:02.034 --> 54:04.829
You were at the house, and I saw you.

54:04.996 --> 54:08.165
The best thing you can do
is get out of here.

54:08.791 --> 54:13.546
I can explain. They picked me up.
I just dumped garbage on your lawn.

54:13.713 --> 54:15.631
- I tried to stop them!
- No.

54:15.840 --> 54:19.260
You dumped garbage on me,
my wife, my little girl.

54:19.427 --> 54:21.178
- I'm sorry.
- Now leave me alone.

54:21.345 --> 54:25.057
What about the game?

54:25.516 --> 54:28.602
I mean, this is the last game.

54:29.395 --> 54:31.272
Please.

54:32.148 --> 54:34.483
You've played your last game.

54:44.243 --> 54:47.329
Coach, you are really fucked, man!

54:48.122 --> 54:51.125
No, son. You are.

55:02.887 --> 55:04.346
Lisa!

55:07.016 --> 55:12.980
How about it, Lis? I was at
band practice today watching you.

55:13.147 --> 55:17.067
- You're real good.
- Yeah, I saw you there, Stef.

55:18.277 --> 55:23.157
Maybe I'll join the band to spend
more time with you. How's that sound?

55:23.324 --> 55:26.494
It sounds like Nickerson
didn't take you back.

55:26.660 --> 55:31.499
Screw Nickerson. I've got the grades,
the talent. I'll get my scholarship.

55:31.665 --> 55:35.961
You'll get your football scholarship,
I'll get nothing.

55:36.128 --> 55:38.172
What are you talking about?

55:39.465 --> 55:44.887
Asshole jocks who can't spell their
names get scholarships and I can't.

55:45.054 --> 55:46.931
Asshole jocks?

55:47.389 --> 55:52.061
An asshole who'd scream at his
girlfriend who he says he loves...

55:52.228 --> 55:54.605
...in front of a busload of people.

55:54.772 --> 55:58.150
- I don't need to be treated like that!
- Wait, Lisa.

55:58.317 --> 56:02.071
I apologize. A lot was going on.
You don't understand.

56:02.238 --> 56:05.366
I don't understand?
You don't understand!

56:05.908 --> 56:10.496
I want to go to college and study
music. But we can't afford it.

56:10.663 --> 56:15.793
Nobody in Ampipe gets a music
scholarship, just football scholarships!

56:16.335 --> 56:18.754
So I'll be a grocery clerk.

56:22.341 --> 56:29.014
